Notes / divergences from §5.3 + §7:
  - `created_by` references public.accounts(id), not public.users(id). The
    plan's prose says "users" but this codebase uses accounts as the principal
    entity (matches earlier C.1 approvals + cloud_runs convention). Already
    flagged as project memory.
  - All 4 new tables have RLS enabled. Read policies attached to
    automations + automation_versions for workspace_member visibility;
    composio_triggers and trigger_event_log have no SELECT policy (only
    accessed via service-role API code) — RLS will deny reads from
    authenticated/anon roles, which is the safe default.
  - The cloud_runs.triggered_by CHECK was made nullable-tolerant
    (NULL OR IN (...)) so the 100 pre-existing rows don't violate the
    constraint. Future manual/scheduled/webhook-triggered runs set it explicitly.
  - cloud_runs.inputs default is '{}'::jsonb so the api code can write
    inputs unconditionally without nullability bookkeeping.
